===Etymology===
Origin unknown; said to have been [[w:thieves' cant|thieves’ cant]] for “lightning”.

Also formerly written "giffy", to which a connection with [[gliff]] has been proposed. <ref>The Vocabulary of East Anglia: An Attempt to Record the Vulgar Tongue of the Twin Sister Counties, Norfolk and Suffolk, As It Existed in the Last Twenty Years of the Eighteenth Century, And Still Exists; With Proof Of Its Antiquity From Etymology And Authority</ref>

